  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dd3.\u0d91\u0db8\u0dca.\u0d95.\u0d92 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d85\u0d9f\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "GMOA warns",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Health has informed the Government Medical Officers' Association to take necessary measures from now on as there is a possibility of spreading the Omacron 2.75 variant of Corona in Sri Lanka which is currently spreading across India.",
        "Dr. Haritha Aluthge, editor of the Government Medical Officers' Association, says that the Ministerial Technology Advisory Committee has been informed to gather immediately and take the necessary measures as there is a situation where the people will not be able to pay attention to the disease if it spreads in the country's economic crisis.",
        "Dr. Aluthge also mentioned that although this variety has not been reported from Sri Lanka, early preparation is important.",
        "The Ministry of Health has also been informed to encourage the people who have not received all three vaccines to get vaccinated."
      ],
